## Description

IPscalper is a tool for gathering open-source information about IP addresses. It integrates various APIs to retrieve data such as geographical location, reputation, and association with known threats.

## Installation

No installation is required. Simply clone the repository and run the script.

## Usage

```
usage: IPscalper [-h] [-all] [-v] [-geo] [-raw] [-vt] [-abuse] [-otx]
                 [-showkeys] [-criminalip] [-c2]
                 IP

A tool for finding open source information about IP addresses. All tools
used in this script are free, although API keys are necessary for some of
them. To obtain the keys, you need to create an account for the respective APIs. Be mindful of API limits. I am not responsible for any misuse of APIs or tools used in this script.

positional arguments:
  IP                   IP address to be searched

optional arguments:
  -h, --help           show this help message and exit
  -all                 Use all available tools
  -v, --verbose        Enable verbose output
  -geo, --location     Use IP-api to get IP location (no key needed)
  -raw                 Display raw JSON output
  -vt, --VirusTotal    Use VirusTotal API for information (key required -> edit
                       API_keys.txt file or uncomment lines)
  -abuse, --AbuseIPdb  Use AbuseIPdb API for information (key required -> edit
                       API_keys.txt file or uncomment lines)
  -otx, --AlienVault   Use OTX AlienVault API for information (key required -> edit
                       API_keys.txt file or uncomment lines)
  -showkeys            Display API keys
  -criminalip          Use CriminalIP API for information (key required -> edit
                       API_keys.txt file or uncomment lines)
  -c2, --Feodo         Check if IP is in Abuse.ch Feodo tracker last 30 days
                       C2 IoCs (no key needed)
```

## Requirements

- Python 3
- Internet connection (some features require API access)
- API keys for certain features (refer to the Usage section)

## Disclaimer

I am not responsible for any misuse of APIs or tools used in this script. Use responsibly and respect API usage limits.

